3. For each position in the second string, find the index of the corresponding position in the first string. If it does not exist, add the character to the second sequence at that position.
4. If either sequence is longer than the other, the longer sequence is the LCS. If the sequences are the same length, then the LCS is the sequence that is the same in both sequences.

